Sentencas: NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+delta (NBCFd) layered perovskites are investigated as cathodes in Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effects of Fe doping (up to 20%) and Ba deficiency (up to 10%) are explored.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The compounds are prepared via molten citrate route and characterized by XRPD, SEM, TGA and cerimetric titration.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties are tested via 4-probe conductivity measurement and impedance experiments on symmetric cells at varying temperature (550 degrees C-700 degrees C) and O-2 pressure (5%-100% v/v).
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The compositional tailoring leads to activity variation and distinct oxygen reduction behavior.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: An ordered layered structure with tetragonal lattice (P4/mmm) is found, whose cell volume increases with Fe doping and decreases with Ba deficiency.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: High total conductivity (150-450 S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C) is measured despite the hindering effect of Fe.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In stoichiometric compounds, Fe doping reduces the polarization resistance, while an increase is observed in Ba-deficient samples.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The impedance results are rationalized by distribution of relaxation times analysis and equivalent circuit modeling, which reveal that the steps of surface electronation and ion transfer across the electrode/electrolyte interface are determining.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Acting on electronation, Fe doping influences the electrode's activity.
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The target performance for application is achieved at 10% Ba deficiency and 5% Fe doping (0.14 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C).
Titulo: Structural and Electrochemical Characterization of NdBa1-xCo2-yFeyO5+δ as Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
